WE do not care how long the circus in the MDC continues, with regards to who has mass appeal and takes over. As far as we were told, the late MDC founding leader Morgan Tsvangirai appointed Nelson Chamisa. By Tongai Torira, Our Reader The Thokozani Khupe-led MDC-T says Chamisa’s takeover in 2018 after being appointed deputy president in 2016 was wrong. <iframe width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/qM7MbfRoJ9o?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe> Let them try all tricks, we will not be hoodwinked. No matter how frequent Khupe dines with Tsvangirai’s grave, this will not sway voters to support a traitor. If people had preferred her, they would have voted for her during the 2018 elections. Voters cannot be forced by courts or documents that can be amended.